<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,944,1114]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,944,970]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks</emphasis>
. No specimens of this species were examined. 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[792,955,944,970]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38096" refString="Distant, W. L. (1908) Rhynchota-Homoptera. In: Bingham, C. T. (Ed.), The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma, IV, pp. i-xv + 1 - 501." type="book chapter" year="1908">Distant (1908)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on specimens collected from 
<collectingRegion box="[321,397,980,1006]" country="India" name="Assam" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Assam</collectingRegion>
and Nilgiri Hills. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nielson, M. W." box="[605,775,980,1006]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 318" refId="ref38619" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1982) A revision of the subfamily Coelidiinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) IV. Coelidiini. Pacific Insects Monograph, 38, 1 - 318." type="journal article" year="1982">Nielson (1982)</bibRefCitation>
adequately described and illustrated the species. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" box="[336,439,1016,1042]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Olidiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis box="[336,439,1016,1042]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">O. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in being deeply piceous with a broad flavous longitudinal band at the basal half of the costa of the forewing and by the aedeagus with a long subapical spine that extends beyond the shaft midlength (
<figureCitation box="[159,251,1088,1114]" captionStart="FIGURES 34" captionStartId="69.[151,264,1963,1988]" captionTargetBox="[205,1396,265,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@69.[151,1436,209,1922]" captionTargetPageId="69" captionText="FIGURES 34 A–Q. Species of Olidiana McKamey, male genitalia.A–E. O. genista (Nielson); F–I O. multispinata (Nielson); J–M. O. nocturna (Distant); N–Q. O. opulenta (Distant): Modified and reproduced from Nielson (1982)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366612/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Figs. 34</figureCitation>
L–M).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
